  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Contribution to the Construction of a Building to House the Municipal Administration of Beni</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The municipal town hall of Beni in the Democratic Republic of the Congo was destroyed by protestors in November 2019, resulting in a diminished level of municipal services. The current project provides supplementary funding to an existing IOM-led stabilization consortium in Beni, to ensure that the construction of the new municipal building corresponds with the expectations and requests of the provincial and local governments. This allows the local government to resume the delivery of municipal administrative services to the population of Beni. To ensure full transparency throughout the construction process, monitoring is conducted by an inclusive committee consisting of the local administration, civil society and youth representatives, as well as the United Nations Organization Stabilization Mission in the Democratic Republic of the Congo (MONUSCO) and IOM.</narrative>
  </description>
